quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  3,171,"They are joyful for receiving God‚Äôs grace and bounty, and that God does not deny the reward of the believers"
  3,172,"ňĻAs forňļ those who responded to the call of God and His Messenger after their injury,¬†those of them who did good and were mindful ňĻof Godňļ will have a great reward"
  3,173,"Those who were warned, ‚ÄúYour enemies have mobilized their forces against you, so fear them,‚ÄĚ the warning only made them grow stronger in faith and they replied, ‚ÄúGod ňĻaloneňļ is sufficient ňĻas an aidňļ for us and ňĻHeňļ is the best Protector.‚ÄĚ"
  3,174,"So they returned with God‚Äôs favours and grace, suffering no harm. For they sought to please God. And surely God is ňĻtheňļ Lord of infinite bounty"
  3,175,"That ňĻwarningňļ was only ňĻfromňļ Satan, trying to prompt you to fear his followers.¬†So do not fear them; fear Me if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  3,176,"ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Do not grieve for those who race to disbelieve‚ÄĒsurely they will not harm God in the least. It is God‚Äôs Will to disallow them a share in the Hereafter, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  3,177,"Those who trade belief for disbelief will never harm God in the least, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  3,178,"Those who disbelieve should not think that living longer is good for them. They are only given more time to increase in sin, and they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  3,179,"God would not leave the believers in the condition you were in, until He distinguished the good from the evil ňĻamong youňļ. Nor would God ňĻdirectlyňļ reveal to you the unseen,¬†but He chooses whoever He wills as a messenger. So believe in God and His messengers. And if you are faithful and mindful ňĻof Godňļ, you will receive a great reward"
  3,180,"And do not let those who ňĻgreedilyňļ withhold God‚Äôs bounties think it is good for them‚ÄĒin fact, it is bad for them! They will be leashed ňĻby their necksňļ on the Day of Judgment with whatever ňĻwealthňļ they used to withhold. And God is the ňĻsoleňļ inheritor of the heavens and the earth. And God is All-Aware of what you do"
  3,181,"Indeed, God has heard those ňĻamong the Jewsňļ who said, ‚ÄúGod is poor; we are rich!‚ÄĚ We have certainly recorded their slurs and their killing of prophets unjustly. Then We will say, ‚ÄúTaste the torment of burning"
  3,182,This is ňĻthe rewardňļ for what your hands have done. And God is never unjust to ňĻHisňļ creation.‚ÄĚ
  3,183,"Those ňĻare the same peopleňļ who say, ‚ÄúGod has commanded us not to believe in any messenger unless he brings us an offering to be consumed by fire ňĻfrom the skyňļ.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúOther prophets did in fact come to you¬†before me with clear proofs and ňĻevenňļ what you demanded‚ÄĒwhy then did you kill them, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  3,184,"If you are rejected by them, so too were messengers before you who came with clear proofs, divine Books, and enlightening Scriptures"
  3,185,"Every soul will taste death. And you will only receive your full reward on the Day of Judgment. Whoever is spared from the Fire and is admitted into Paradise will ňĻindeedňļ triumph, whereas the life of this world is no more than the delusion of enjoyment"